abstract.0: Chart Industries, a global equipment manufacturer, wanted to deliver faster and more efficient service to its customers by removing roadblocks hidden in its core Oracle’s JD Edwards 9.2 business processes. In this session learn how the business is leveraging intelligent software to evaluate manual touches in its processes, improve working capital, and delight customers. See how process mining technology can quickly lead to dramatic business transformation and improve customer experience.
abstract.1:
Kansas City Power & Light (KCP&L) found itself operating two autonomous and highly customized information systems after acquiring a competing electricity and natural gas distributor. With increasing disruptive forces challenging the utilities industry, KCP&L wanted to modernize its operations by uniting its IT infrastructure in order to deliver a new standard of excellence for customers. In this session hear how PwC leveraged Oracle technologies to help solve KCP&L’s problems through a single integrated customer information system solution that supported the business’ long-term organizational vision.

Attend this session and enter for a chance to win 1 of 3 - $500 AMEX gift cards!
abstract.2:
The world is undergoing a vast transformation with digital disruption creating both unprecedented growth opportunities and high risks of failure. Competing successfully requires a new way of doing business, and building a powerful ecosystem of trusted partners is more important than ever before. Hitachi and Oracle—together an Industrial IoT powerhouse—bring together each company’s strengths to create digital business solutions built on top of a world-class IoT platform. In this session see real-world examples that show how this unmatched combination allows each company to deliver on their commitment to creating a better world and ultimately driving business results while making a positive impact on society.

Attend This Session and Enter for a Chance to Win One of Three US$500 AMEX Gift Cards!
abstract.3:
In this session explore how organizations can drive exciting business outcomes with intelligent automation. Like many IT trends, automation can be applied without understanding or solving the underlying problem. Learn how data science, process optimization, and leading-edge technologies such as artificial intelligence and machine learning can drive operational savings while releasing funds to enable digital innovation.

Attend This Session and Enter for a Chance to Win a US$1,500 AMEX Gift Card!
abstract.4: The spectacular rise of the internet transformed every aspect of life and work. To stay relevant and grow in an ever-changing and disruptive environment, businesses need to be reimagined. Digital is the key to reconnect and elevate customer experience. This transformation is as much about changing mindsets and acquiring new skills as it is about leveraging digital technologies. It is about reinventing business functions and processes for today’s digital consumer with a roadmap to achieve desired business outcomes. Enterprises that succeeded in amplifying customer experience went beyond traditional ways to modernize the core and refactor talent. Attend this session to learn more.
abstract.5:
Data is defining the future of our industry. Many have been talking about the data deluge and how it is the new oil. This exponential growth in data puts huge demands on compute, network, and storage. Intel and Oracle have been collaborating for years to bring next-generation technologies to help customers transform their business in the face of demanding workloads. Join this session to get insights on future cloud technologies, and get a sneak peek into Intel’s Optane DC Persistent Memory and Oracle’s TimesTen In-Memory Database.

Attend this session and enter for a chance to win a Oculus Rift Virtual Reality System + Acer Predator Intel Core i7 Gaming Laptop Bundle!
abstract.6:
Building the intelligent enterprise of the future requires successfully navigating complex digital transformations in this Business 4.0 era. The world’s leading enterprises are driving this across four areas: Enhancing customer experience and enabling mass personalization with intelligent automation, bolstering innovation by connecting collaborative ecosystems in the cloud, fueling growth strategies and embracing risk with deep analytics and contextual insights, and redefining traditional business models by enabling enterprise agility to create exponential value. In this session discover how enterprises including GE Healthcare, Knowles, McDermott International, and Scottish Water are positioning themselves to lead their industries in defining the future of business.

Attend this session and enter for a chance to win 1 of 3 - $500 AMEX gift cards!

0.bio: Alexander Rinke is an enterprise software entrepreneur. He co-founded Celonis in 2011 and serves as co-CEO and Chief Product Owner. Celonis became one of the fastest growing enterprise software companies in the world, helping customers such as Siemens, 3M, Dow Chemicals, Vodafone and many others save millions through improving their core business processes. As an actively involved early stage technology investor, Alexander helped to found other enterprise software companies – such as Testbirds and Talentry. Alexander has always been an entrepreneur at heart and founded his first company, a tuition agency, at the age of 14. For his entrepreneurial achievements, Alexander has recently been listed in the Forbes 30 under 30 list of top achievers under the age of 30. 3.bio:
Greg Dietrich serves as vice president, Operations Engineering & Excellence, for DXC Technology’s (NYSE: DXC), global delivery organization. 

Greg leads the DXC team responsible for the continual transformation of the company’s delivery capability, applying “intelligent automation” to make DXC the most efficient, effective and valued corporation in the IT Services industry.

This multi-million dollar cultural change program leverages the latest thinking in data science, process optimization and leading edge technologies. (e.g., artificial intelligence, machine learning) to drive over $300m in operational savings while increasing client satisfaction. 

Prior to re-joining CSC, now DXC Technology, in August 2016, Greg was a Managing Director at Credit Suisse in their Finance, Operations and IT division, based in New York.  In this role, Greg led a technology transformation program to reduce operational risk, cost and complexity across their enterprise systems and tools.

Before that, Greg worked at CSC, IBM and GE in various roles and is a graduate of GE's prestigious Information Management Leadership Program. 

Greg holds an M.B.A. from Columbia Business School in New York, a B.S. in Industrial & Management Engineering from RPI, and certificates in Executive Leadership and Change Leadership from Cornell University's Johnson Graduate School of Management.

5.bio:
Raejeanne B. Skillern is vice president in the Data Center Group and general manager of the Cloud Service Provider Platform Group at Intel Corporation. She manages Intel’s business, roadmap and customer engagements for public cloud infrastructure deployments and leads the team responsible for working closely with the world’s largest cloud service providers to optimize Intel’s data center solutions for their unique needs.

Before assuming her current position in 2014, Skillern was director of marketing for big data and cloud computing at Intel. She was responsible for creating new business opportunities, developing and optimizing products, and establishing industry thought leadership for Intel in these segments. During her six-year tenure in that role, she spearheaded the creation of the Open Data Center Alliance, a global IT consortium intended to serve as the voice of IT requirements for open data center technology, and led the team that successfully extended the Intel brand to cloud services through the Powered by Intel Cloud Technology program. Earlier in her Intel career, Skillern held various leadership roles in product marketing, strategic analysis, demand creation and business development. She also spent two years with Intel Online Services, an Intel subsidiary that provided co-location and managed hosting services.

Skillern earned her bachelor’s degree in mathematics and computer science from Pepperdine University and her MBA from Marylhurst University.

6.bio:
Akash Khurana is the Global Vice President, Chief Information Officer and Chief Digital Officer for McDermott. 

Akash has more than 20 years of IT experience, where his most recent assignment before joining McDermott was as the Senior IT Director of Global Product Lines and Regional P&Ls at Baker Hughes. He has also served in a variety of progressive leadership roles at GE Healthcare and Power & Water divisions. He began his career as an Enterprise Resource Planning Business Consultant and a technology leader at a leading retail company in the late 1990s. Akash joined McDermott in April 2015 where he has been leading business transformation as the CIO and CDO of the Global Information Technology and Digital organization. 
He has been featured in major publications including Forbes, Gartner, ZDNet, Energy CIO Insights, Computerworld 2017 Top 100 Chief Information Officers, and was most recently named 2018 Houston CIO of the Year and CIO100. Akash also holds an Advisory Board Member position with SymphonyAI, the world’s largest & fastest growing Artificial Intelligence (AI) company, focused on building innovative solutions for the industrial vertical.  
Akash is recognized as a technology leader for his vision, developing the right talent, streamlining processes and ensuring that IT delivers integrated strategic technology solutions aligned to business needs. 

Education

Akash has a Bachelor’s of Science Degree in Engineering from the University of Pune, India, and a Master of Business Administration from the University of Wisconsin. He is a qualified Six Sigma Master Black Belt and Lean Leader.
